Import
fitnesse.fixtures

SetUp Plugins=fitnesse.testsystems.slim.CustomTableAliasPlugin Plugins=fitnesse.testsystems.slim.CustomScriptTableRenderingPlugin CustomComparators=glob:fitnesse.testsystems.slim.GlobComparator

Library
page driver
echo fixture

script hash fixture
send as hash
subkey subval
$nested<-[
subkey subval
]		 hash
send as hash
key1 value1
key2 $nested->[
subkey subval
]
$myHashMap0<-[
key1 value1
key2
subkey subval
]		 hash
send as hash
key1 value2
key2
subkey subval2
$myHashMap<-[
key1 value2
key2
subkey subval2
]		 hash


Java hashmap symbol's value

script echo fixture
check echo $`myHashMap0.key1`->[value1] value1
check echo $`myHashMap0.key2.subkey`->[subval] subval
check echo $`myHashMap0.key3`->[null] null
check echo $`myHashMap.key1`->[value2] value2
check echo $`myHashMap.key2.subkey`->[subval2] subval2
check echo $`myHashMap.key3`->[null] null
check echo $`myHashMap3.key1`->[Unable to evaluate: myHashMap3.key1; ReferenceError: "myHashMap3" is not defined in at line number 1] /Unable to evaluate: myHashMap3.key1; .+/ found in: Unable to evaluate: myHashMap3.key1; ReferenceError: "myHashMap3" is not defined in <eval> at line number 1

Reverse (use expression value as expected value)
script echo fixture
check echo value1 $`myHashMap0.key1`->[value1]
check echo subval $`myHashMap0.key2.subkey`->[subval]
check echo null $`myHashMap0.key3`->[null]
check not echo value3 $`myHashMap.key1`->[value2]
check echo subval2 $`myHashMap.key2.subkey`->[subval2]
check echo null $`myHashMap.key3`->[null]

Hashtable symbol (i.e. String) as value
script echo fixture
$myHashMap2<-[
key1 value2
key2
subkey subval1
]		 echo
key1 value2
key2
subkey subval1
check echo $`myHashMap2.key1`->[value2] value2
check echo value2 $`myHashMap2.key1`->[value2]
check echo $`myHashMap2.key2.subkey`->[subval1] subval1
check echo subval1 $`myHashMap2.key2.subkey`->[subval1]

Other expressions

script echo fixture
check echo $`10+20`->[30] 30
check echo $`myHashMap.size() * 1.5`->[3.0] 3.0
$myStr<-[This is a test] echo This is a test
check echo $`myStr.toUpperCase()`->[THIS IS A TEST] THIS IS A TEST
check echo $`myStr.substr(2,5)`->[is is] is is

Concatenating expressions

script echo fixture
check echo $`1+1`->[2] a 2 a
check echo $`1+1`->[2]a 2a
check echo a$`1+1`->[2]a a2a
check echo this is value1 this is $`myHashMap0.key1`->[value1]


Lists
import
fitnesse.slim.test

script Test Slim With Converter
$myList<-[[a, b, c]] getList
start echo fixture
check echo $`myList.size()`->[3] 3
check echo $`myList.getClass()`->[class java.util.ArrayList] $`myList.getClass()`->[class java.util.ArrayList]
check echo $`myList.getClass()`->[class java.util.ArrayList] class java.util.ArrayList

script Test Slim With Converter
set list converter
$myList2<-[{a, b, c}] getArrayList
start echo fixture
check echo $`myList2.size()`->[Unable to evaluate: myList2.size(); TypeError: myList2.size is not a function in at line number 1] 3
check echo $`myList2.getClass()`->[class java.lang.String] class java.util.ArrayList

Reset list converter to standard one after test

script Test Slim With Converter
remove list converter
